        <p>To convert binary to hex, simply break up the number into groups of 4 digits and convert each group:</p>
        <program language="none"><input>
<p>011011000011    (1731 in decimal)
<inline classes="red">0110</inline><inline classes="blue">1100</inline><inline classes="red">0011</inline>
<inline classes="red">6</inline>   <inline classes="blue">C</inline>   <inline classes="red">3</inline>
6C3             (1731 in decimal)</p>
</input></program>
        <p>To convert hex to binary, we can just turn each hex digit into one group of four binary digits:</p>
        <program language="none"><input>
<p>A1              (161 in decimal)
<inline classes="red">A</inline>   <inline classes="blue">1</inline>
<inline classes="red">1010</inline><inline classes="blue">0001</inline>
10100001        (161 in decimal)</p>
</input></program>
