        <raw format="html" xml:space="preserve">            &lt;h3 class="underlined"&gt;
               Why Hexadecimal
            &lt;/h3&gt;
            </raw>
        <p>Why would we want another base system? Large binary values are hard for people to read accurately and remember. Try it yourself - quickly try to decide if 0011100101110110 and 0011100101100110 are the same. Those two binary strings listed above look like this in hex: <m>{3976}_{16}</m> and <m>{3966}_{16}</m> - it is a little easier to say the values and to see where the difference is, isn&#8217;t it? Because changing switching from binary to hex is so easy, hexadecimal is used to display binary values in a more human-readable form. You will see an example of where this is used in web page design on the next page.</p>
        

